metadata.name: Williamsburg #1
metadata.description: Industrial areas mesmerize me. I grew up in a small village in the Alps situated in one of the most beautiful regions of Germany. It was a happy childhood, I loved the outdoors and felt very connected to nature. This came to an abrupt end when my mom left my father. We moved to the industrial area of a small town close to Heidelberg. There was a garbage truck depot right next to the house, a car dealer across the street and a construction company in the basement of our apartment building. I was devastated and heartbroken. I missed nature  and never enjoyed living there but I did like weekends. On weekends industrial areas are completely abandoned. I was roaming the streets and there was lots to discover. It was so quiet on those days that it reminded me on the Alps, the world that I’d loved so much but had to leave behind. As back then, I was wondering the streets of the industrial part of Williamsburg for this project. And again it reminded me on a happy childhood.
